---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Claudia — She catches what you miss">

  <!-- ===================== HERO — FULL BLEED ===================== -->
  <section class="relative min-h-screen overflow-hidden pt-14">
    <!-- Full-bleed hero image -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img
        src="/assets/hero-wide.jpeg"
        alt=""
        class="w-full h-full object-cover object-top"
        loading="eager"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-void via-void/90 to-void/40"></div>
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-void via-transparent to-void/50"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 flex items-center min-h-screen">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <div class="reveal">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-white/[0.06] border border-white/[0.08] rounded-full px-3 py-1.5 mb-8">
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-[#d75050]" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M12 2l2.09 6.26L20.18 9.27l-5.09 3.71L16.18 19.27 12 16l-4.18 3.27 1.09-6.29L3.82 9.27l6.09-1.01z"/></svg>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-paper/60 tracking-wide">Built for Claude Code</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h1 class="reveal reveal-delay-1 text-6xl sm:text-7xl lg:text-[5.5rem] font-extrabold leading-[0.9] tracking-[-0.04em]">
          She catches<br />what you<br /><span class="text-vermillion">miss</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="reveal reveal-delay-2 mt-10 text-xl text-paper/50 leading-relaxed max-w-md font-light">
          You prompt. Claude codes.<br />Claudia makes sure it's actually good.
        </p>

        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-3 mt-12">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 bg-black/40 backdrop-blur-sm border border-white/10 rounded-xl px-5 py-3.5">
            <code id="install-cmd" class="text-sm font-mono text-paper/80 select-all">npm i -g claudia-mentor</code>
            <button id="copy-btn" aria-label="Copy" class="p-1 rounded text-paper/30 hover:text-vermillion transition-colors cursor-pointer">
              <svg class="w-4 h-4" id="copy-icon" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z" /></svg>
              <svg class="w-4 h-4 hidden" id="check-icon" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="reveal reveal-delay-4 mt-6 flex items-center gap-5">
          <a href="https://github.com/reganomalley/claudia" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-sm text-paper/40 hover:text-paper transition-colors">View source</a>
          <span class="text-paper/10">|</span>
          <a href="#how-she-works" class="text-sm text-paper/40 hover:text-paper transition-colors">How it works</a>
          <span class="text-paper/10">|</span>
          <a href="/start" class="text-sm text-vermillion/60 hover:text-vermillion transition-colors">New to this?</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== MARQUEE ===================== -->
  <section class="border-y border-white/[0.06] bg-vermillion overflow-hidden py-4">
    <div class="marquee-track">
      <div class="marquee-content">
        {Array(8).fill(0).map(() => (
          <span class="mx-8 text-sm font-bold tracking-wide text-void/90 uppercase whitespace-nowrap">Every <span class="text-[#D4A574]">Claude</span> needs a <span class="text-void">Claudia</span></span>
        ))}
      </div>
      <div class="marquee-content" aria-hidden="true">
        {Array(8).fill(0).map(() => (
          <span class="mx-8 text-sm font-bold tracking-wide text-void/90 uppercase whitespace-nowrap">Every <span class="text-[#D4A574]">Claude</span> needs a <span class="text-void">Claudia</span></span>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== HOW SHE WORKS ===================== -->
  <section id="how-she-works" class="py-32 sm:py-40">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mb-20">
        <p class="reveal font-mono text-[11px] text-vermillion tracking-[0.25em] uppercase mb-4">How she works</p>
        <h2 class="reveal text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-extrabold leading-[0.95] tracking-[-0.03em]">
          Three ways<br />she shows up
        </h2>
        <p class="reveal mt-6 text-paper/40 leading-relaxed max-w-lg">
          You don't change anything about how you work. Claudia runs alongside Claude Code and steps in when it matters.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Numbered cards -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-0 stagger">
        <div class="reveal border-l border-white/[0.06] pl-8 pr-6 py-2">
          <span class="block text-6xl font-extrabold text-vermillion/20 leading-none mb-4">01</span>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-paper/90 mb-3">Automatic checks</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-paper/40 leading-relaxed">Every time Claude writes a file, Claudia scans it. Leaked API keys get blocked. Bad patterns get flagged. You see what's wrong and how to fix it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal border-l border-white/[0.06] pl-8 pr-6 py-2">
          <span class="block text-6xl font-extrabold text-vermillion/20 leading-none mb-4">02</span>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-paper/90 mb-3">She joins your conversation</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-paper/40 leading-relaxed">Say "I'll use MongoDB for this" and Claudia jumps in: "Actually, Postgres handles this better — here's why." Claude sees her advice and adjusts.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal border-l border-white/[0.06] pl-8 pr-6 py-2">
          <span class="block text-6xl font-extrabold text-vermillion/20 leading-none mb-4">03</span>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-paper/90 mb-3">Ask her directly</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-paper/40 leading-relaxed">11 commands — <code class="text-vermillion/70 text-xs">/claudia:ask</code>, <code class="text-vermillion/70 text-xs">explain</code>, <code class="text-vermillion/70 text-xs">review</code>, <code class="text-vermillion/70 text-xs">why</code>, <code class="text-vermillion/70 text-xs">health</code>, <code class="text-vermillion/70 text-xs">wtf</code>, <code class="text-vermillion/70 text-xs">where</code>, <code class="text-vermillion/70 text-xs">resume</code>, <code class="text-vermillion/70 text-xs">setup</code>, <code class="text-vermillion/70 text-xs">start</code>, <code class="text-vermillion/70 text-xs">shortcuts</code>. She gives you the answer, the tradeoffs, and the reasoning.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== TERMINAL — FULL WIDTH ===================== -->
  <section class="relative py-32 sm:py-40">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-void via-soft-gray/30 to-void pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="max-w-xl mb-16">
        <p class="reveal font-mono text-[11px] text-vermillion tracking-[0.25em] uppercase mb-4">Automatic protection</p>
        <h2 class="reveal text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold leading-[0.95] tracking-[-0.03em]">
          You didn't know this<br />was dangerous. <span class="text-vermillion">She did.</span>
        </h2>
      </div>

      <!-- Full-width terminal -->
      <div class="reveal">
        <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden border border-white/[0.08] shadow-2xl shadow-black/60">
          <div class="bg-[#1a1a1e] px-5 py-3.5 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-[#ff5f57]"></span>
            <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-[#febc2e]"></span>
            <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-[#28c840]"></span>
            <span class="ml-4 text-xs text-paper/20 font-mono">claude</span>
          </div>
          <div id="terminal" class="bg-[#111114] px-6 sm:px-8 py-6 sm:py-8 font-mono text-sm sm:text-[15px] leading-[2]">
            <div class="term-line" style="--delay: 0"><span class="text-[#28c840]">$</span> <span class="text-paper/60">claude</span></div>
            <div class="term-line" style="--delay: 1"><span class="text-paper/45">&gt; Hook up the database with my AWS credentials</span></div>
            <div class="term-line" style="--delay: 2">&nbsp;</div>
            <div class="term-line" style="--delay: 3">
              <span class="text-paper/30">claudia</span>
              <span class="text-[#ff5f57] font-bold ml-2">BLOCKED</span>
              <span class="text-[#febc2e] ml-2">Hardcoded secret detected</span>
            </div>
            <div class="term-line" style="--delay: 4">&nbsp;</div>
            <div class="term-line pl-4" style="--delay: 5"><span class="text-paper/35">Pattern:</span> <span class="text-[#febc2e]">AWS access key (AKIA...)</span></div>
            <div class="term-line pl-4" style="--delay: 6"><span class="text-paper/35">File:</span> <span class="text-paper/55">src/config/database.ts:14</span></div>
            <div class="term-line" style="--delay: 7">&nbsp;</div>
            <div class="term-line pl-4" style="--delay: 8">
              <span class="text-[#28c840] font-bold">Fix:</span>
              <span class="text-paper/50"> Use environment variables. Your secret would have</span>
            </div>
            <div class="term-line pl-4" style="--delay: 9"><span class="text-paper/50">been visible to anyone who clones this repo.</span></div>
            <div class="term-line" style="--delay: 10">&nbsp;</div>
            <div class="term-line pl-4" style="--delay: 11">
              <span class="bg-[#28c840]/10 text-[#28c840] px-3 py-1 rounded inline-block">const db = createPool(process.env.DATABASE_URL)</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== FULL-BLEED BREAK — EYE + TYPOGRAPHY ===================== -->
  <section class="relative py-24 sm:py-32 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 flex flex-col items-center text-center">
      <div class="reveal mb-10">
        <img
          src="/assets/claudia-mascot.png"
          alt="Claudia watching"
          class="w-40 h-40 sm:w-48 sm:h-48 object-contain mascot-float"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
      <p class="reveal text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-extrabold tracking-[-0.03em] leading-[0.95]">
        She's watching<br />every file you write.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== HOOKS LIST ===================== -->
  <section class="py-32 sm:py-40">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[0.4fr_0.6fr] gap-20">
        <div>
          <p class="reveal font-mono text-[11px] text-vermillion tracking-[0.25em] uppercase mb-4">14 hooks. Always on.</p>
          <h2 class="reveal text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight">
            You don't have to<br />remember any of this
          </h2>
          <p class="reveal mt-5 text-paper/40 leading-relaxed">
            7 hooks guard every file Claude writes. 7 more watch your session and teach you as you go. You never run them — they just work.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="reveal font-mono text-[10px] text-paper/25 uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-4">Code guardrails</p>
          <div class="space-y-0 stagger">
            {[
              { name: "Leaked secrets", badge: "Stops it", color: "bg-[#ff5f57]/20 text-[#ff5f57]", desc: "API keys, passwords, and tokens that should never be in code" },
              { name: "Broken git", badge: "Stops it", color: "bg-[#ff5f57]/20 text-[#ff5f57]", desc: "Writing to .env, leaving merge conflict markers" },
              { name: "Bad code patterns", badge: "Warns you", color: "bg-[#febc2e]/15 text-[#febc2e]", desc: "eval(), empty catch blocks, console.log in production" },
              { name: "Sketchy dependencies", badge: "Warns you", color: "bg-[#febc2e]/15 text-[#febc2e]", desc: "Deprecated, hacked, or pointlessly small packages" },
              { name: "Docker mistakes", badge: "Warns you", color: "bg-[#febc2e]/15 text-[#febc2e]", desc: "Running as root, using :latest, missing optimizations" },
              { name: "Accessibility gaps", badge: "Warns you", color: "bg-[#febc2e]/15 text-[#febc2e]", desc: "Images without alt text, buttons without labels" },
              { name: "License conflicts", badge: "Warns you", color: "bg-[#febc2e]/15 text-[#febc2e]", desc: "GPL code sneaking into your MIT project" },
            ].map((h) => (
              <div class="reveal flex items-start gap-4 py-4 border-b border-white/[0.04]">
                <span class={`shrink-0 mt-0.5 text-[10px] font-mono font-medium px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full ${h.color}`}>{h.badge}</span>
                <div>
                  <span class="text-sm font-medium text-paper/80">{h.name}</span>
                  <span class="text-sm text-paper/30 ml-2">{h.desc}</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>

          <p class="reveal font-mono text-[10px] text-paper/25 uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mt-10 mb-4">Proactive coaching</p>
          <div class="space-y-0 stagger">
            {[
              { name: "Keyword teaching", badge: "Teaches", color: "bg-[#28c840]/15 text-[#28c840]", desc: "Spots unfamiliar tech in Claude's output and offers plain-English explanations" },
              { name: "Prompt coaching", badge: "Coaches", color: "bg-[#28c840]/15 text-[#28c840]", desc: "Detects vague prompts like \"fix it\" and shows you how to ask better" },
              { name: "Session greeting", badge: "Greets", color: "bg-[#28c840]/15 text-[#28c840]", desc: "Welcomes you on startup with a rotating tip and your current context" },
              { name: "Compaction tips", badge: "Teaches", color: "bg-[#28c840]/15 text-[#28c840]", desc: "Explains what just happened when Claude auto-compacts your conversation" },
              { name: "Run suggestions", badge: "Helps", color: "bg-[#28c840]/15 text-[#28c840]", desc: "Claude creates a file, Claudia tells you how to run it" },
              { name: "Next steps", badge: "Guides", color: "bg-[#28c840]/15 text-[#28c840]", desc: "Suggests 2-3 things you could do next so you never hit a dead end" },
              { name: "Milestones", badge: "Cheers", color: "bg-[#28c840]/15 text-[#28c840]", desc: "Notices your first commit, first deploy, first test — and tells you what they mean" },
            ].map((h) => (
              <div class="reveal flex items-start gap-4 py-4 border-b border-white/[0.04]">
                <span class={`shrink-0 mt-0.5 text-[10px] font-mono font-medium px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full ${h.color}`}>{h.badge}</span>
                <div>
                  <span class="text-sm font-medium text-paper/80">{h.name}</span>
                  <span class="text-sm text-paper/30 ml-2">{h.desc}</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== ASK HER ANYTHING — HORIZONTAL SCROLL ===================== -->
  <section class="py-32 sm:py-40 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 mb-12">
      <p class="reveal font-mono text-[11px] text-vermillion tracking-[0.25em] uppercase mb-4">Ask her anything</p>
      <h2 class="reveal text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-extrabold leading-[0.95] tracking-[-0.03em]">
        You don't need the answer.<br /><span class="text-paper/25">Just the question.</span>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <!-- Horizontal scroll cards -->
    <div class="overflow-x-auto scrollbar-hide pb-4">
      <div class="flex gap-4 px-6 w-max stagger">
        {[
          { q: "Where should I store my data?", detail: "Postgres, Mongo, Redis, Pinecone — she'll tell you which one and why.", topic: "Databases" },
          { q: "How do I add login to my app?", detail: "Auth0 vs rolling your own, sessions vs JWT, OAuth flows explained.", topic: "Security" },
          { q: "Should I use AWS or Vercel?", detail: "Where to host, when serverless makes sense, how to not get a surprise bill.", topic: "Infrastructure" },
          { q: "React or Svelte for this?", detail: "Framework picking, SSR vs SPA, state management without the headache.", topic: "Frontend" },
          { q: "REST or GraphQL?", detail: "Which API style, how to handle pagination, when you need real-time.", topic: "API Design" },
          { q: "What should I even test?", detail: "What's worth testing, what's a waste of time, which testing tools to use.", topic: "Testing" },
          { q: "Why is my app so slow?", detail: "Where to look first, common bottlenecks, how to measure before you guess.", topic: "Performance" },
          { q: "How do I deploy this?", detail: "CI/CD from scratch, GitHub Actions patterns, monitoring that matters.", topic: "DevOps" },
          { q: "How should I structure this data?", detail: "Schema design, migrations without downtime, indexes that actually help.", topic: "Data Modeling" },
          { q: "How do I ask Claude for what I actually want?", detail: "Claudia detects vague prompts and rewrites them into instructions that get results.", topic: "Prompt Coaching" },
        ].map((d) => (
          <div class="reveal w-72 shrink-0 bg-white/[0.03] border border-white/[0.06] rounded-xl p-6 hover:border-vermillion/20 transition-colors group">
            <p class="text-sm font-medium text-paper/80 group-hover:text-vermillion transition-colors leading-snug">"{d.q}"</p>
            <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-paper/30 leading-relaxed">{d.detail}</p>
            <p class="mt-4 text-[10px] font-mono text-vermillion/30 uppercase tracking-widest">{d.topic}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== PROMPT COACHING — THINKING IMAGE ===================== -->
  <section class="py-32 sm:py-40">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[0.55fr_0.45fr] gap-20 items-center">
        <div class="order-2 lg:order-1">
          <p class="reveal font-mono text-[11px] text-vermillion tracking-[0.25em] uppercase mb-4">Better prompts = better code</p>
          <h2 class="reveal text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-extrabold leading-[0.95] tracking-[-0.03em]">
            The difference<br />between "fix the<br />auth" and <span class="text-vermillion">getting<br />what you want</span>
          </h2>
          <p class="reveal mt-6 text-paper/40 leading-relaxed">
            Most vibe coders leave 80% of Claude's power on the table because they don't know how to ask. Claudia notices when your prompt is too vague and shows you how to rewrite it.
          </p>

          <div class="reveal mt-10 space-y-4">
            <div class="border border-white/[0.06] rounded-xl p-5">
              <p class="text-[10px] font-mono text-paper/25 uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-3">What you typed</p>
              <p class="text-base text-paper/40 line-through decoration-vermillion/30 decoration-2">"Fix the auth"</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border border-vermillion/20 bg-vermillion/[0.03] rounded-xl p-5">
              <p class="text-[10px] font-mono text-vermillion/50 uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-3">What Claudia suggests</p>
              <p class="text-base text-paper/70 leading-relaxed">"Refactor the auth middleware to use async/await, add error handling for expired tokens, and return 401 responses with JSON error codes."</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="reveal order-1 lg:order-2 relative">
          <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
            <img src="/assets/hands-keyboard.jpg" alt="Hands on keyboard" class="w-full h-auto" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <div class="absolute -bottom-6 -left-6 w-32 h-32 bg-vermillion/10 rounded-full blur-3xl pointer-events-none"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== BEGINNER MODE ===================== -->
  <section class="py-32 sm:py-40 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[0.45fr_0.55fr] gap-20 items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="reveal font-mono text-[11px] text-vermillion tracking-[0.25em] uppercase mb-4">Never coded before?</p>
          <h2 class="reveal text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-extrabold leading-[0.95] tracking-[-0.03em]">
            She meets you<br />where <span class="text-vermillion">you</span> are
          </h2>
          <p class="reveal mt-6 text-paper/40 leading-relaxed max-w-md">
            Set experience to "beginner" and Claudia transforms. No command lists. No jargon. She waits until you need her, then shows up with exactly the right thing.
          </p>
          <div class="reveal mt-8">
            <div class="bg-black/40 rounded-lg p-4 font-mono text-sm">
              <span class="text-paper/30">~/.claude/claudia-context.json</span>
              <pre class="text-paper/60 mt-2"><code>{'{ "experience": "beginner" }'}</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4 stagger">
          <div class="reveal border border-white/[0.06] bg-white/[0.015] rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-paper/80 mb-1">Stuck detection</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-paper/30">Type "I'm stuck" or "idk" and she asks one clarifying question, then gives you one small next step. No overwhelm.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="reveal border border-white/[0.06] bg-white/[0.015] rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-paper/80 mb-1">Run suggestions</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-paper/30">Claude creates a file, Claudia tells you how to run it. <code class="text-paper/50">open index.html</code>, <code class="text-paper/50">python3 app.py</code> — the stuff you wouldn't know to type.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="reveal border border-white/[0.06] bg-white/[0.015] rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-paper/80 mb-1">Milestones</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-paper/30">"First commit. Your code has a save point now." She notices when you hit real milestones and tells you what they mean.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="reveal border border-white/[0.06] bg-white/[0.015] rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-paper/80 mb-1">Progressive reveal</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-paper/30">Commands appear only when they're relevant. Write a file, she mentions <code class="text-paper/50">/claudia:explain</code>. Hit an error, she mentions <code class="text-paper/50">/claudia:wtf</code>. No firehose.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="reveal border border-white/[0.06] bg-white/[0.015] rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-paper/80 mb-1">Next-step suggestions</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-paper/30">After Claude finishes something, Claudia suggests 2-3 things you could do next. No dead ends.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== FINAL CTA — BOLD ===================== -->
  <section class="relative py-32 sm:py-40 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-vermillion"></div>

    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="reveal text-5xl sm:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-extrabold tracking-[-0.04em] leading-[0.9] text-void">
